"1443–Overleden","1455–1532":"1455–1532","1463–1509":"1463–1509","–Male":"Overleden","–Female":"Overleden","1455":"1455","1532":"1532","1443":"1443","01 Jan 1460":"1463","1463":"1463","Abt 1314":"circa 1314","1509":"1509","Abt 1418":"circa 1418","1418":"1418","Artane, County Dublin, Ireland":"Artane, County Dublin, Ierland","Tartayne Dublin Dublin Leinster Ireland":"Diocese of Dublin, Ierland","Artain, Dublin, Ireland":"Artane, County Dublin, Ierland","Ballgriffin, Dublin":"Dublin, Ierland","Kilkenny, County Kilkenny, Ireland":"Kilkenny, County Kilkenny, Ierland"},"en":{"Abt 1418–":"about 1418–Deceased","1418–Male":"1418–Deceased","1418–Female":"1418–Deceased","1443–Female":"1443–Deceased","1455–1532":"1455–1532","1463–1509":"1463–1509","–Male":"Deceased","–Female":"Deceased","1455":"1455","1532":"1532","1443":"1443","01 Jan 1460":"1463","1463":"1463","Abt 1314":"about 1314","1509":"1509","Abt 1418":"about 1418","1418":"1418","Artane, County Dublin, Ireland":"Artane, County Dublin, Ireland","Tartayne Dublin Dublin Leinster Ireland":"Diocese of Dublin, Ireland","Artain, Dublin, Ireland":"Artane, County Dublin, Ireland","Ballgriffin, Dublin":"Dublin, Ireland","Kilkenny, County Kilkenny, Ireland":"Kilkenny, County Kilkenny, Ireland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Holywood","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Irish: of Norman origin, possibly a habitational name from Hollywood, Dublin.","Irish: adopted for Gaelic <b>Ó Cuileannáin</b> ‘descendant of <i>Cuileannán</i>’, a personal name apparently based on a diminutive of <i>cuileann</i> ‘holly tree’, and more commonly Anglicized as   Cullinan   or   Cullen  .","English: possibly a habitational name from any of various farms or hamlets in England called <i>Hollywood</i>, such as one in Sandon and Burston (Staffordshire), perhaps named with Middle English <i>holli</i> ‘holly’ + <i>wode</i> ‘wood’. However, the place is not on record before 1775, and all Hollywoods appear to be late."],"variants":[{"name":"Cullinan","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Cormac.","Irish (Clare): Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Cuileannáin</b> ‘descendant of <i>Cuileannán</i>’, from a diminutive of <i>Cuileann</i> (see   Cullen   2)."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Holywood was born about 1418, in Artane, County Dublin, Ireland as the son of Roger Holywood and HOLYWOOD. He had at least 1 son and 3 daughters with Elizabeth Isabel Plunkett. He died in his hometown."},"et":{"Abt 1418–":"umbes 1418–Surnud","1418–Male":"1418–Surnud","1418–Female":"1418–Surnud","1443–Female":"1443–Surnud","1455–1532":"1455–1532","1463–1509":"1463–1509","–Male":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1455":"1455","1532":"1532","1443":"1443","01 Jan 1460":"1463","1463":"1463","Abt 1314":"umbes 1314","1509":"1509","Abt 1418":"umbes 1418","1418":"1418","Artane, County Dublin, Ireland":"Artane, County Dublin, Iirimaa","Tartayne Dublin Dublin Leinster Ireland":"Diocese of Dublin,